name: micheal-o/CDMA_Network_Simulator
description: This project simulates the effect of implementing an admission control algorithm in a 10km radius CDMA cell. It completely simulates the entire process required by 10,000 (can be increased/decreased) moving customers to make phone calls, by connecting to a basestation with limited traffic channels. It also simulates interference at every 10x10m square within the cell and produces the basestation load statistics. The program makes all the necessary computations such as EIRP, received signal level, path loss, SINR, interference level, fading, shadowing etc.
